# cli profile
- This is a single-user developer CLI tool. Do not flag threats that
  require the user to attack their own environment or configuration files.
- Do not flag TOCTOU or race conditions that assume concurrent invocation.
- Do not flag security concerns about qx{} or system() calls where the
  input originates from the user's own configuration file.
- Assume perlcritic and perltidy are enforced; do not flag anything
  those tools would catch.
- Do not flag security concerns about files that are part of the
  installed distribution itself. These are as trusted as the
  source code.
